            <!-- Contents -->
            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">A record of the discussions on various topics which Ibn Sawdakīn (d. 646) had with his master Ibn ʿArabī. The content includes that of K. al-Wasāʾil by Ibn Sawdakīn (RG 436), which is really an extract of this longer work.</note>
               <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
               <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">OY states that there are no extant mss of this work, but three copies have now been found: the earliest is Zahiriyya 16632, which is in the hand of al-Farghānī, probably dateable to 660s. There are also much later less reliable copies in the Budeiri library, 142, and in the Dar al-Kutub, Cairo, Taymur 147. Further mss identified by JC: Damascus al-Assad (http://www.alassad-library.gov.sy/Search_makhtotat2013.php): 16627/2 which follows IA’s ʿAqīda, dated 955.</note>
